    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Kind of related to that. It is the terminology used in the spec \"Interop Standards in Eth2 PM\", https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-pm/tree/master/interop\r\n\r\nBut really it is not about the actual network connectivity, but configuring nodes with the same test data, i.e. same genesis block, same validator keys. In lieu of having an actual Eth1 deposit contract and link.\r\n\r\nWill be useful for live testing of the API and honest validator, so that there is a chain with Eth1 data (mocked), I have a key for the validator to use, etc.\r\n\r\nThere is a second part, to loading a specific state from an input file (SSZ or YAML), in order to test specific conditions. That is a separate work item. There are also several different ways to specify, e.g. generate the known validator keys vs loading them from a pre-generated file. (also in the other work item).\r\n\r\nThis work item is to get just a basic mocked start up of a chain (and is already partially working, but crashes generating the 4th key).",
